The paper deals with hyperparameter search, which is a common problem in machine learning. The proposed approach is evaluated on various tasks such as attend/infer/repeat, video next frame segmentation forecasting, and progressive generative adversarial networks, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
